{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C and grease a baking dish (26 cm x 24 cm x 5 cm).","Place whipping cream and butter into mixing bowl and heat <nobr>3 min\/90°C\/speed 1.5<\/nobr>. Transfer to a small bowl and set aside.","Insert butterfly whisk. Place 200 g golden caster sugar and eggs in mixing bowl and mix <nobr>3 min\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Add plain flour, cooled reserved butter and cream mixture and mix <nobr>20 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Remove butterfly whisk.","Add cooking apples and use spatula to stir apple slices into pudding mix. Transfer to prepared baking dish.","Place a small bowl on mixing bowl lid and weigh in blackberries and remaining 20 g sugar, then scatter blackberries and sugar over pudding mix. Bake 50-55 minutes (180°C) or until golden. Serve warm; it's lovely with a little cream."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["170 g butter, diced, plus extra for greasing","250 g whipping cream","220 g golden caster sugar","3 large eggs","300 g plain flour","500 g cooking apples, peeled, cored and cut in slices (1 cm)","250 g blackberries","200 g single cream, for serving (optional)"]}],"id":"r76283","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-LECXoEz18uQ\/XZaoCoEGYpI\/AAAAAAAAhGc\/vjoFd5Dpch8eBsRSpqfCckplFID80y-QACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_clmzFJFHcwly0PeI.png","title":"Apple and Blackberry Pudding","publishedAt":"2015-09-14T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"7.3 g","fat":"33 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"64.8 g","calories":"2449 kJ \/ 585 kcal"},"usefulItems":"rectangular baking dish (26 cm x 24 cm x 5 cm), oven","basicInfo":["easy","25m","1h 15m","8 portions"]}